# Line-ending policy: this repo is LF-canonical (everything committed is LF).
#
# Without this, GitHub's Windows runners -- which default to core.autocrlf=true --
# convert the LF blobs to CRLF on checkout, and `gofmt -l` then flags every .go file
# (CI gofmt gate fails). An explicit `eol=lf` attribute overrides core.autocrlf and
# pins the working tree to LF everywhere, matching what's stored. No local churn:
# the working tree is already LF.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Toolchain-critical: Go source must be LF (gofmt's canonical form). PowerShell is
# fine with LF on both 5.1 and 7+, so the .ps1 snippets stay LF too.
*.go   text eol=lf
*.ps1  text eol=lf

# Never normalize the built binary.
*.exe  binary
